# Cloudflare Pages routing
#
# /s/<id> share links are now handled by functions/s/[id].js — see comment
# inside that file for why we use a Function instead of an HTML rewrite
# (TL;DR: Cloudflare strips .html and breaks rewrites that target HTML).
#
# /share (bare, no ID) bounces home, since the only legit share URLs end
# in an 8-char ID like /s/ABC12345.
/share          /    302
